  .docs-content

    h1 Framework7 MCP Server

    p Framework7 provides an <a href="https://modelcontextprotocol.io/" target="_blank">MCP (Model Context Protocol)</a> server that allows AI assistants and tools to query the Framework7 API documentation programmatically.

    p With the MCP server, AI tools like Claude, Cursor, Windsurf, and other MCP-compatible clients can:

    ul
      li Search across Framework7 parameters, methods, events, and CSS variables
      li Get full API documentation for any component
      li Look up specific parameters, methods, or events
      li Retrieve CSS custom properties grouped by theme
      li Browse and retrieve demo source code for Core, Vue, React, and Svelte

    h2 How It Works

    p The MCP server exposes a JSON-RPC 2.0 endpoint at <code>https://framework7.io/mcp</code>. MCP-compatible clients connect to this endpoint and can call any of the 9 available tools to retrieve Framework7 API information.

    p The server provides access to:
    ul
      li <b>68 components</b> with their full API (parameters, methods, events)
      li <b>CSS variables</b> for 57 components with iOS and Material Design theme values
      li <b>Demo source code</b> for all available demos across 4 framework variants

    h2 Available Tools

    p The MCP server provides the following tools:

    table
      thead
        tr
          th Tool
          th Description
      tbody
        tr
          td <code>list-components</code>
          td List all available Framework7 components and modules
        tr
          td <code>get-component</code>
          td Get full API for a component (parameters, events, methods, CSS variables)
        tr
          td <code>search-api</code>
          td Fuzzy search across parameters, methods, events, and CSS variables
        tr
          td <code>get-parameter</code>
          td Get details for a specific parameter/option
        tr
          td <code>get-method</code>
          td Get details for a specific method (instance or app-level)
        tr
          td <code>get-event</code>
          td Get details for a specific event (instance, app, or DOM)
        tr
          td <code>get-css-variables</code>
          td Get CSS custom properties for a component by theme
        tr
          td <code>list-demos</code>
          td List all available demos with slugs and frameworks
        tr
          td <code>get-demo</code>
          td Get demo source code for a specific framework variant

